description.narrative:
-  Mobilize & sensitize women’s groups : 5 vegetable and 8 rice producing groups (1,140 women), 2 women’s groups dedicating to milk production. 2 milk processing WLSEEs . 1 WLSEE  “energy shop” -  1 women’s group of 20 women producing milk.
- Establish Savings & Loans Schemes (SLS)
- Structure SHGs into WLSEEs :5 vegetable producing groups and the 7 WLSEEs (6 WLSEEs processing vegetable (2), rice (2), and milk (2), and the energy shop)training, registration;
- Provide financial support to WLSEEs  2 MFI;
-  Establish WLSEEs’ RF and monitor its functioning,
- Agree with WLSEEs on SET to introduce & sub-products to sell  ;
- Link the WLSEEs to SET suppliers;
- Train journalists & organise exposure visits to supported WLSEEs ;
- Produce IEC materials on SE ; 
- Carry out awareness-raising activities at all levels
- Train key stakeholders on SE policy matters and Advocacy;
- Produce evidence from achievements & policy briefs to inform platforms and authorities ;
- Support strategic policy and advocacy work involving media; 
- Set-up M&E system integrating innovative tools  ;
- Document & disseminate learning
